Broth: In a large saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add shallot and sauté for 2 minutes or until softened. Add chicken broth, ginger, curry powder, turmeric, cayenne pepper and cumin; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes to allow flavors to blend. Add mango to broth and simmer, uncovered, for another 5 minutes. Transfer broth to fondue pot, setting flame to keep at a simmer. Spear chicken with fondue fork and fondue for 2 to 4 minutes or until cooked through. Serve with… Thai peanut sauce, red curry paste, mango salsa or chutney.